  "output": "## Test Coverage Analysis — jobsquare\n\n**Current state: 0% coverage.** No `tests/` directory, no test files, no test framework installed (`requirements.txt` has only `httpx` and `PyYAML`). The `fetchers.py` docstring even claims the design is \"unit-testable against mocked transports\" via the injectable `httpx.AsyncClient` — but nothing exercises that.\n\n### Recommended setup (one-time)\n```\npip install pytest pytest-asyncio respx freezegun\n```\n- `respx` mocks `httpx` at the transport layer (matches the injectable-client design already in place).\n- `freezegun` needed for anything touching `datetime.now()` (recency filters, `_iso_now`, dedup timestamps).\n- `pytest.ini` / `pyproject.toml`: set `asyncio_mode = auto` for `pytest-asyncio`.\n\n---\n\n### 1. `models.py` — `parse_posted_at`, `Job`\n\nHighest-value target: every fetcher depends on this, and the docstring calls out three incompatible formats it must reconcile.\n\n**Gaps:**\n- Empty/`None` input → `None`\n- Epoch seconds vs. epoch milliseconds boundary (the `>= 1e12` heuristic) — untested at the boundary\n- ISO-8601 with `Z` suffix, with explicit offset, and *without* any tzinfo (should default to UTC)\n- Garbage string (Workday's `\"Posted 3 Days Ago\"`) → `None`, not an exception\n- Negative epoch (`lstrip(\"-\").isdigit()` branch) — is this reachable/correct?\n- `Job.key` stability under fields that mutate (title/location) — key must *not* include those\n- `Job.content_hash` — verify it changes when title/location/url/department change, and does NOT change when `posted_at`/`salary_range` change (would cause spurious \"changed\" notifications otherwise — untested assumption)\n- `Job.to_row()` drops `raw`, adds `key`/`content_hash`\n\n```python\n# tests/test_models.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import timezone\nfrom models import Job, parse_posted_at\n\n\nclass TestParsePostedAt:\n    def test_empty_returns_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"\") is None\n        assert parse_posted_at(None) is None\n\n    def test_epoch_seconds(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1700000000\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_epoch_milliseconds(self):\n        # Lever-style 13-digit ms epoch\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1643241332430\")\n        assert dt.year == 2022\n\n    @pytest.mark.parametrize(\"digits\", [\"999999999999\", \"1000000000000\"])\n    def test_seconds_vs_milliseconds_boundary(self, digits):\n        # 1e12 - 1 must be treated as seconds; 1e12 as milliseconds\n        dt = parse_posted_at(digits)\n        assert dt is not None  # pin down expected year per branch\n\n    def test_iso8601_with_z_suffix(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_iso8601_naive_defaults_to_utc(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_iso8601_with_explicit_offset_preserved(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00+05:00\")\n        assert dt.utcoffset().total_seconds() == 5 * 3600\n\n    def test_unparseable_prose_returns_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"Posted 3 Days Ago\") is None\n\n    def test_whitespace_only_stripped(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"   \") is None  # currently: strip() -> \"\" -> falsy? verify\n\n\nclass TestJob:\n    def _job(self, **over):\n        base = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                    title=\"Engineer\", url=\"https://x/1\")\n        return Job(**{**base, **over})\n\n    def test_key_ignores_mutable_fields(self):\n        j1 = self._job(title=\"Engineer I\")\n        j2 = self._job(title=\"Engineer II\")\n        assert j1.key == j2.key  # same source/company/external_id\n\n    def test_content_hash_changes_on_title(self):\n        j1 = self._job(title=\"Engineer\")\n        j2 = self._job(title=\"Senior Engineer\")\n        assert j1.content_hash != j2.content_hash\n\n    def test_content_hash_stable_across_unrelated_fields(self):\n        j1 = self._job(posted_at=\"2024-01-01\")\n        j2 = self._job(posted_at=\"2024-06-01\")\n        assert j1.content_hash == j2.content_hash  # posted_at not in hash blob\n\n    def test_to_row_drops_raw_adds_key_and_hash(self):\n        j = self._job(raw={\"secret\": 1})\n        row = j.to_row()\n        assert \"raw\" not in row\n        assert row[\"key\"] == j.key\n        assert row[\"content_hash\"] == j.content_hash\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `filters.py` — `match`, `filter_jobs`\n\n**Gaps:**\n- Exclude takes priority over include (both matching same job)\n- Include with no match → dropped; include empty/None → passes everyone\n- Location matching is substring/case-insensitive, not exact\n- Recency cutoff: job with unparseable `posted_at` must be **kept**, not dropped (explicit design comment — no test proves it)\n- Word-boundary regex: partial-word false positives (e.g. exclude \"eng\" shouldn't match \"Engineering\"? — actually `\\b` matches word-boundary at \"eng\" inside \"engineering\" only if \"eng\" isn't full word... need to verify actual regex behavior since `\\beng\\b` won't match inside \"engineering\")\n- `filter_jobs` with `max_age_days` absent vs. `0`\n\n```python\n# tests/test_filters.py\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nimport pytest\nfrom models import Job\nfrom filters import match, filter_jobs\n\n\ndef _job(title=\"Senior Engineer\", location=\"Remote - USA\", department=\"\"):\n    return Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                title=title, url=\"https://x/1\", location=location, department=department)\n\n\nclass TestMatch:\n    def test_no_filters_passes(self):\n        assert match(_job()) is True\n\n    def test_exclude_wins_over_include(self):\n        j = _job(title=\"Senior Sales Engineer\")\n        assert match(j, include=[\"engineer\"], exclude=[\"sales\"]) is False\n\n    def test_include_keyword_required(self):\n        assert match(_job(title=\"Product Manager\"), include=[\"engineer\"]) is False\n\n    def test_include_word_boundary_no_partial_match(self):\n        # \"eng\" should not match inside \"Engineering\" due to \\b\\bEND\n        assert match(_job(title=\"Engineering Lead\"), include=[\"eng\"]) is False\n\n    def test_location_substring_case_insensitive(self):\n        assert match(_job(location=\"San Francisco, CA\"), locations=[\"san francisco\"]) is True\n\n    def test_location_no_match_excluded(self):\n        assert match(_job(location=\"London, UK\"), locations=[\"USA\"]) is False\n\n    def test_recency_cutoff_drops_old_job(self):\n        j = _job()\n        j.posted_at = (datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=30)).isoformat()\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=7)\n        assert match(j, cutoff=cutoff) is False\n\n    def test_recency_cutoff_keeps_unparseable_posted_at(self):\n        j = _job()\n        j.posted_at = \"Posted 3 Days Ago\"  # Workday prose, unparseable\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=7)\n        assert match(j, cutoff=cutoff) is True  # must not be nuked\n\n\nclass TestFilterJobs:\n    def test_max_age_days_filters_list(self):\n        fresh = _job(title=\"A\")\n        stale = _job(title=\"B\")\n        stale.posted_at = (datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=100)).isoformat()\n        result = filter_jobs([fresh, stale], {\"max_age_days\": 7})\n        assert stale not in result\n\n    def test_no_rules_returns_all(self):\n        jobs = [_job(title=\"A\"), _job(title=\"B\")]\n        assert filter_jobs(jobs, {}) == jobs\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. `store.py` — `Store.diff`, migration, `added_since`\n\nMost important integration-adjacent gap: `diff()` is the entire dedup contract.\n\n**Gaps:**\n- New job → appears in `new`, row inserted\n- Same job, same `content_hash`, re-run → `last_seen` bumps, appears in neither list\n- Same job, changed `content_hash` → appears in `changed`, row updated (not duplicated)\n- `_migrate()` — opening a DB file created before `salary_range` existed adds the column without data loss (needs a fixture pre-populated via raw `sqlite3` without that column)\n- `added_since` ordering and strict `>` (not `>=`) boundary — a row with `first_seen == ts` must be excluded\n- `get_meta`/`set_meta` upsert (`ON CONFLICT`) — second `set_meta` call overwrites, doesn't duplicate row\n- Context manager closes connection on exit even if `diff` raises\n\n```python\n# tests/test_store.py\nimport sqlite3\nimport pytest\nfrom store import Store\nfrom models import Job\n\n\ndef _job(ext_id=\"1\", title=\"Engineer\"):\n    return Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=ext_id,\n               title=title, url=f\"https://x/{ext_id}\")\n\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef store(tmp_path):\n    with Store(tmp_path / \"test.db\") as s:\n        yield s\n\n\nclass TestDiff:\n    def test_new_job_returned_and_inserted(self, store):\n        new, changed = store.diff([_job()])\n        assert len(new) == 1 and not changed\n        assert store.count() == 1\n\n    def test_unchanged_job_not_in_either_list(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job()])\n        new, changed = store.diff([_job()])\n        assert not new and not changed\n        assert store.count() == 1  # no duplicate row\n\n    def test_changed_content_updates_row_not_insert(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job(title=\"Engineer I\")])\n        new, changed = store.diff([_job(title=\"Engineer II\")])\n        assert not new\n        assert len(changed) == 1\n        assert store.count() == 1\n\n    def test_last_seen_bumps_on_rerun(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job()])\n        row1 = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT last_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()\n        store.diff([_job()])\n        row2 = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT last_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()\n        assert row2[\"last_seen\"] >= row1[\"last_seen\"]\n\n\nclass TestMigration:\n    def test_adds_salary_range_column_to_legacy_db(self, tmp_path):\n        path = tmp_path / \"legacy.db\"\n        conn = sqlite3.connect(str(path))\n        conn.executescript(\"\"\"\n            CREATE TABLE jobs (key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, source TEXT, company TEXT,\n                external_id TEXT, title TEXT, url TEXT, location TEXT,\n                department TEXT, employment_type TEXT, posted_at TEXT,\n                content_hash TEXT, first_seen TEXT, last_seen TEXT);\n            CREATE TABLE meta (k TEXT PRIMARY KEY, v TEXT);\n        \"\"\")\n        conn.commit(); conn.close()\n\n        with Store(path) as s:\n            cols = {r[\"name\"] for r in s.conn.execute(\"PRAGMA table_info(jobs)\")}\n            assert \"salary_range\" in cols\n\n\nclass TestMeta:\n    def test_set_meta_upserts_not_duplicates(self, store):\n        store.set_meta(\"last_scan\", \"2024-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\")\n        store.set_meta(\"last_scan\", \"2024-02-01T00:00:00+00:00\")\n        assert store.get_meta(\"last_scan\") == \"2024-02-01T00:00:00+00:00\"\n        n = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM meta WHERE k='last_scan'\").fetchone()[0]\n        assert n == 1\n\n    def test_get_meta_missing_key_returns_none(self, store):\n        assert store.get_meta(\"nope\") is None\n\n\nclass TestAddedSince:\n    def test_strict_greater_than_excludes_boundary(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job()])\n        ts = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT first_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()[\"first_seen\"]\n        assert store.added_since(ts) == []  # boundary itself excluded\n\n    def test_ordering_oldest_first(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job(\"1\"), _job(\"2\")])\n        rows = store.added_since(\"2000-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\")\n        assert [r[\"first_seen\"] for r in rows] == sorted(r[\"first_seen\"] for r in rows)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. `notify.py` — all five notifiers, especially the untested Twilio path\n\n**Gaps (this is the module with the most silent-failure