        "content": "\nHighest-value target: every fetcher depends on this, and the docstring calls out three incompatible formats it must reconcile.\n\n**Gaps:**\n- Empty/`None` input → `None`\n- Epoch seconds vs. epoch milliseconds boundary (the `>= 1e12` heuristic) — untested at the boundary\n- ISO-8601 with `Z` suffix, with explicit offset, and *without* any tzinfo (should default to UTC)\n- Garbage string (Workday's `\"Posted 3 Days Ago\"`) → `None`, not an exception\n- Negative epoch (`lstrip(\"-\").isdigit()` branch) — is this reachable/correct?\n- `Job.key` stability under fields that mutate (title/location) — key must *not* include those\n- `Job.content_hash` — verify it changes when title/location/url/department change, and does NOT change when `posted_at`/`salary_range` change (would cause spurious \"changed\" notifications otherwise — untested assumption)\n- `Job.to_row()` drops `raw`, adds `key`/`content_hash`\n\n```python\n",
