        "content": "\nMost important integration-adjacent gap: `diff()` is the entire dedup contract.\n\n**Gaps:**\n- New job → appears in `new`, row inserted\n- Same job, same `content_hash`, re-run → `last_seen` bumps, appears in neither list\n- Same job, changed `content_hash` → appears in `changed`, row updated (not duplicated)\n- `_migrate()` — opening a DB file created before `salary_range` existed adds the column without data loss (needs a fixture pre-populated via raw `sqlite3` without that column)\n- `added_since` ordering and strict `>` (not `>=`) boundary — a row with `first_seen == ts` must be excluded\n- `get_meta`/`set_meta` upsert (`ON CONFLICT`) — second `set_meta` call overwrites, doesn't duplicate row\n- Context manager closes connection on exit even if `diff` raises\n\n```python\n",
