        "title": "7. `agent.py` — deterministic helpers (LLM-free, fully testable)",
        "content": "\n**Gaps — this is the second-highest-risk module** because `cmd_db_new`'s group-boundary truncation logic and the watermark contract have subtle invariants that a naive test would miss:\n\n- `cmd_db_new` first run (no marker) uses `--since-days` window\n- `cmd_db_new` truncation happens **only at `first_seen` group boundaries** — never splits a batch (this is the core untested invariant; a naive `LIMIT`-style truncation would silently drop half a batch)\n- `cmd_db_new` watermark returned is the *last included group's* timestamp, not `--now`\n- `cmd_db_mark` rejects a non-ISO watermark (exit code 2, stderr message)\n- `cmd_db_mark --now` vs explicit watermark — mutually exclusive-ish handling; neither given → exit code 2\n- `_normalize_ats` — replacements happen in text nodes only, **not** inside tags/`<style>`/`<script>` (explicit design invariant, zero test proof)\n- `_normalize_ats` — counts dict tallies per rule label correctly\n- `cmd_pdf_render` — missing input file → exit code 2, no crash\n- `cmd_pdf_render` — PDF magic-byte check catches a failed render (mock `subprocess.run`)\n- `main()` argv dispatch: bare invocation → interactive; `-i` flag anywhere → interactive; mode words stop at first flag\n\n```python\n",
        "level": 3
      },
      {
        "title": "tests/test_agent.py",
        "content": "import json\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nimport agent\nfrom store import Store\nfrom models import Job\n\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef sources_yaml(tmp_path):\n    db = tmp_path / \"jobs.db\"\n    p = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    p.write_text(f\"sources: []\\ndb: {db}\\n\")\n    return p\n\n\nclass TestCmdDbNew:\n    def test_first_run_uses_since_days_window(self, sources_yaml, capsys):\n        with Store(agent.load_config(sources_yaml)[\"db\"]) as s:\n            s.diff([Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                         title=\"A\", url=\"https://x/1\")])\n        agent.cmd_db_new([\"-c\", str(sources_yaml), \"--since-days\", \"7\"])\n        out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n        assert out[\"first_run\"] is True\n        assert out[\"count\"] == 1\n\n    def test_truncation_never_splits_a_first_seen_group(self, sources_yaml, capsys):\n        # two jobs inserted in the same diff() call share one first_seen timestamp;\n        # limit=1 must still include both (or neither) — never just one.\n        with Store(agent.load_config(sources_yaml)[\"db\"]) as s:\n            s.diff([Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=str(i),\n                         title=f\"J{i}\", url=f\"https://x/{i}\") for i in range(2)])\n        agent.cmd_db_new([\"-c\", str(sources_yaml), \"--since-days\", \"7\", \"--limit\", \"1\"])\n        out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n        assert out[\"count\"] in (0, 2)  # never 1\n        if out[\"count\"] == 0:\n            assert out[\"truncated\"] is True\n\n    def test_watermark_is_last_included_group_not_now(self, sources_yaml, capsys):\n        ...  # insert two batches at different times, assert watermark == first batch's ts\n             # when the second batch is truncated out\n\n\nclass TestCmdDbMark:\n    def test_rejects_non_iso_watermark(self, sources_yaml, capsys):\n        rc = agent.cmd_db_mark([\"not-a-date\", \"-c\", str(sources_yaml)])\n        assert rc == 2\n\n    def test_now_flag_sets_current_timestamp(self, sources_yaml):\n        rc = agent.cmd_db_mark([\"--now\", \"-c\", str(sources_yaml)])\n        assert rc == 0\n        with Store(agent.load_config(sources_yaml)[\"db\"]) as s:\n            assert s.get_meta(agent.MARK_KEY) is not None\n\n    def test_no_args_returns_error(self, sources_yaml):\n        rc = agent.cmd_db_mark([\"-c\", str(sources_yaml)])\n        assert rc == 2\n\n\nclass TestNormalizeAts:\n    def test_smart_quotes_replaced_in_text(self):\n        html, counts = agent._normalize_ats(\"<p>\\u201cHello\\u201d</p>\")\n        assert html == '<p>\"Hello\"</p>'\n        assert counts[\"smart-double-quote\"] == 2\n\n    def test_tag_attributes_untouched(self):\n        html, _ = agent._normalize_ats('<div data-x=\"\\u2014\">text</div>')\n        assert 'data-x=\"\\u2014\"' in html  # inside a tag, must not be replaced\n\n    def test_style_block_content_untouched(self):\n        html, counts = agent._normalize_ats(\n            \"<style>.x::before{content:'\\u2014'}</style><p>a\\u2014b</p>\")\n        assert \"content:'\\u2014'\" in html  # style block preserved verbatim\n        assert counts.get(\"em-dash\") == 1  # only the <p> occurrence counted\n\n    def test_no_replacements_needed_empty_counts(self):\n        html, counts = agent._normalize_ats(\"<p>plain ascii text</p>\")\n        assert counts == {}\n\n\nclass TestCmdPdfRender:\n    def test_missing_input_file_returns_2(self, tmp_path, capsys):\n        rc = agent.cmd_pdf_render([str(tmp_path / \"nope.html\")])\n        assert rc == 2\n\n    def test_failed_render_detected_by_missing_pdf_magic(self, tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n        src = tmp_path / \"in.html\"\n        src.write_text(\"<html><body>x</body></html>\")\n        monkeypatch.setattr(agent, \"_chrome_bin\", lambda: \"/bin/true\")\n        class FakeResult:\n            stderr = \"chrome crashed\"\n        monkeypatch.setattr(agent.subprocess, \"run\", lambda *a, **k: FakeResult())\n        rc = agent.cmd_pdf_render([str(src)])\n        assert rc == 1  # out file never written -> no %PDF magic bytes\n```\n\n---\n\n",
